pdnIgmpStdExtMIB.name: pdnIgmpStdExtMIB

revisions.description: Added pdnIgmpGeneralQueryInterval object to configure this timer globally rather than per interface.
Added pdnIgmpSnoopingSelection to enabled/disable Igmp snooping on a system-wide basis.
Corrected a type where pdnIgmpIngerfaceLeaveJoinForwardingDelay should have been pdnIgmpInterfaceLeaveJoinForwardingDelay.

pdnIgmpStdExtMIB.organization: Paradyne Networks MIB Working Group Other information about group editing the MIB.
pdnIgmpStdExtMIB.contactinfo: Paradyne Networks, Inc. 8545 126th Avenue North Largo, FL 33733 www.paradyne.com General Comments to: mibwg_team@paradyne.com Editor(s) Clay Sikes, Jesus Pinto
pdnIgmpStdExtMIB.description: This MIB module is a supplement to the IGMP-STD-MIB.

pdnIgmpInterfaceExtEntry.name: pdnIgmpInterfaceExtEntry
pdnIgmpInterfaceExtEntry.description: An extended entry in the igmpInterfaceTable. Each entry corresonds to a particular interface.

pdnIgmpInterfaceSnoopEnableDisable.name: pdnIgmpInterfaceSnoopEnableDisable
pdnIgmpInterfaceSnoopEnableDisable.description: This object specifies whether or not IGMP Snooping is enabled or disabled. enabled(1) - IGMP Snooping is Enabled disabled(2) - IGMP Snooping is Disabled

pdnIgmpInterfaceLeaveDelay.name: pdnIgmpInterfaceLeaveDelay
pdnIgmpInterfaceLeaveDelay.description: This object specifies the leave-delay period. This value is defened as the period of time during which a multicast stream will continue to be forwarded on an interface after receipt of an IGMP leave message for that stream.

pdnIgmpInterfaceLeaveJoinForwardingDelay.name: pdnIgmpInterfaceLeaveJoinForwardingDelay
pdnIgmpInterfaceLeaveJoinForwardingDelay.description: This object specifies the leave-join-delay period. This value is defined as the period of time during which new multicast streams will not be forwarded on a port following the receipt of an IGMP Leave message.

pdnIgmpCacheExtEntry.name: pdnIgmpCacheExtEntry
pdnIgmpCacheExtEntry.description: An extended entry in the igmpCacheTable. Each entry corresonds to a particular IP Multicast Group Destination Address on a particular interface.

pdnIgmpCacheStatsMulticastPktsIn.name: pdnIgmpCacheStatsMulticastPktsIn
pdnIgmpCacheStatsMulticastPktsIn.description: The total number of IP Multicast packets received excluding IGMP messages.

pdnIgmpCacheStatsMulticastPktsOut.name: pdnIgmpCacheStatsMulticastPktsOut
pdnIgmpCacheStatsMulticastPktsOut.description: The total number of IP Multicast packets transmitted excluding IGMP messages.

pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpQueriesIn.name: pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpQueriesIn
pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpQueriesIn.description: The total number of IGMP Query messages received.

pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpQueriesOut.name: pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpQueriesOut
pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpQueriesOut.description: The total number of IGMP Query messages transmitted.

pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpReportsIn.name: pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpReportsIn
pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpReportsIn.description: The total number of IGMP Report messages received.

pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpReportsOut.name: pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpReportsOut
pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpReportsOut.description: The total number of IGMP Report messages transmitted.

pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpLeavesIn.name: pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpLeavesIn
pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpLeavesIn.description: The total number of IGMP Leave messages received.

pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpLeavesOut.name: pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpLeavesOut
pdnIgmpCacheStatsIgmpLeavesOut.description: The total number of IGMP Leave messages transmitted.

pdnIgmpSnoopingSelection.name: pdnIgmpSnoopingSelection
pdnIgmpSnoopingSelection.description: This object specifies whether or not IGMP Snooping is enabled or disabled on a system-wide basis. enabled(1) - IGMP Snooping is Enabled on the device disabled(2) - IGMP Snooping is Disabled on the device

pdnIgmpGeneralQueryInterval.name: pdnIgmpGeneralQueryInterval
pdnIgmpGeneralQueryInterval.description: This object is similar to the igmpInterfaceQueryInterval object defined in RFC2933. However, it can be used to set a global value that applies to all the interfaces in the system with IGMP enabled. A value of zero disables this option and thus the agent shall employ the value configured in the igmpInterfaceQueryInterval for each interface running IGMP. In the other hands, if this object is set to a value greater than zero, the value takes precedence over the value configured in the igmpInterfaceQueryInterval for that interface.

pdnIgmpStdExtMIBCompliance.name: pdnIgmpStdExtMIBCompliance
pdnIgmpStdExtMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for IP Multicast products which implement the pdnIpMcaseMIB.

pdnIgmpStdExtMIBComplianceV2.name: pdnIgmpStdExtMIBComplianceV2
pdnIgmpStdExtMIBComplianceV2.description: The compliance statement for Ip products which implement the IGMP protocol.

pdnIgmpStdExtConfigGroup.name: pdnIgmpStdExtConfigGroup
pdnIgmpStdExtConfigGroup.description: Objects grouped for configuring IP Multicast and IGMP parameters.

pdnIgmpStdExtStatsGroup.name: pdnIgmpStdExtStatsGroup
pdnIgmpStdExtStatsGroup.description: Objects grouped for IP Multicast and IGMP Statistics.

pdnIgmpStdExtGeneralConfigGroup.name: pdnIgmpStdExtGeneralConfigGroup
pdnIgmpStdExtGeneralConfigGroup.description: Objects grouped for general configuring of IP Multicast and IGMP parameters. This group has been deprecated in favor of pdnIgmpStdExtGeneralConfigGroupV2.

pdnIgmpStdExtGeneralConfigGroupV2.name: pdnIgmpStdExtGeneralConfigGroupV2
pdnIgmpStdExtGeneralConfigGroupV2.description: Objects grouped for general configuring of IP Multicast and IGMP parameters.
